b'' b'dressner) writes:' b'' b' i have a gateway with a floppy. the drive only reads files it' b' wrote to the floppy. floppies that have been formatted and' b' contain files from other machines are unreadable. also, floppies' b' that were written by this defective floppy drive a long time ago are' b' also unreadable.' b'' b' this sounds like a head alignment problem.' b'' b'too right it does!' b'' b' how does one go about' b' fixing it? are there alignment screws that you can adjust?' b'' b'the --very very first-- thing you do is make sure that --all-- files on' b"the floppies that you can currently read in the drive, which aren't" b'already on your hd or another floppy (if you have -two- floppy drives)' b'get copied to your hd (and/or to a floppy in your other drive).' b'' b"if you don't do this before fixing the alignment problem you have kissd" b'those files goodbye. (well, you can -try- to re-misalign the drive back' b"to read your floppies, but don't count on be able to do so!)" b'' b"generally, head alignment is something i'd only trust to a good repair" b'shop (though there are/have been diy guides).' b'' b'+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+' b'nick fitzgerald, pc applications consultant, csc, uni of canterbury, n.z.' 